In the semi-supervised graph partition, the graph is partitioned into subgraphs by (1) maximizing similarity of nodes within each subgraph, (2) encouraging in accordance to prior knowledge, such as partially manually labeled data points, and (3) enhancing spatial connectedness of partitioned clusters, which was preliminarily described in our previous study45. In particular, the overall similarity of nodes within \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
