To obtain a brain parcellation with spatially and functionally consistent clusters, it is desired that voxels within each cluster of a brain parcellation are spatially connected. The connectedness can be guaranteed by satisfying the topological property of the cluster using geodesic star convexity shape79. The geodesic shape enforces a voxel in each cluster that is connected to all other voxels of the cluster by at least one geodesic path entirely included in the cluster, i.e., any pair of voxels from the cluster can be linked by a geodesic path that is entirely within the cluster. For a parcellation of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
